Macropterous female:
Similar to brachypterous female in general structure and colouration but slightly narrower in form (
Fig. 25
); body length 17.40, maximum width (across basal abdomen) 11.10. Pronotum with posterolateral angles less produced, obtuse (
Fig. 25
); scutellum enlarged, tumid; hemelytra with clavus well defined (
Fig. 25
), claval vein evident, membrane present and well defined, lacking evident venation.
